120
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:44,160
It's highly contagious,no known cure.

121
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:48,660
Really,no one mentioned this to you?

122
00:05:48,730 --> 00:05:50,500
It's okay,

123
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:53,030
as long as you've had no physical contact,

124
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:54,700
it should be fine.

125
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:58,060
Don't go anywhere.

126
00:05:58,130 --> 00:05:59,730
I'm going to look into this.

127
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:10,260
Don't worry... there's no such thing as a type 5 c-vector.

128
00:06:10,330 --> 00:06:12,430
I said that to scare

129
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:14,030
them off so I could talk to you in private.

130
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:15,830
My name's Jacob Hood.

131
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:19,830
I'm kind of the science guy for the FBI.

132
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:22,860
My family... are they going to be okay?

133
00:06:22,930 --> 00:06:24,360
Is the same thing gonna happen to me?

134
00:06:24,430 --> 00:06:26,100
I don't know.

135
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:28,160
That's what I'm here to find out.

136
00:06:28,230 --> 00:06:31,260
The police,they think that...

137
00:06:31,330 --> 00:06:33,700
I didn't do anything

138
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:36,330
to my mom,my dad or my little brother.

139
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,560
I know.

140
00:06:37,630 --> 00:06:39,630
You do?

141
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:41,360
Yeah.

142
00:06:41,430 --> 00:06:43,130
The forensic pathologists,they've been over

143
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,730
your house with a fine-toothed comb to find

144
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:47,130
anything that would've caused your family's paralysis.

145
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,530
So if you're a poisoner,you're a very good one.

146
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:53,160
And I've seen your high school transcripts,

147
00:06:53,230 --> 00:06:55,930
and Chemistry,well,you failed it,twice.

148
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,160
So I don't think you're too much of a threat.

149
00:06:58,230 --> 00:07:00,630
What I want to know is,is there anything

150
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:02,600
you can remember that you did differently

151
00:07:02,660 --> 00:07:04,030
from your family yesterday morning?

152
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:05,400
Anything at all?

153
00:07:05,460 --> 00:07:07,800
No.

154
00:07:07,860 --> 00:07:11,030
All we did was eat breakfast.

155
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:12,960
Just breakfast.

156
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:27,200
We've already got forensics.

157
00:07:27,260 --> 00:07:29,130
Want to tell me again why we're here?

158
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:32,060
Any idea,Rachel,how many

159
00:07:32,130 --> 00:07:34,800
seemingly innocuous household ingredients

160
00:07:34,860 --> 00:07:35,930
could actually kill you?

161
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,800
Air freshener?

162
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:41,960
Smells good.

163
00:07:42,030 --> 00:07:44,800
Key ingredient: formaldehyde.

164
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:47,630
Could cause headaches,

165
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:49,230
nausea,nosebleeds,

166
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:51,400
dizziness,memory loss...

167
00:07:51,460 --> 00:07:53,400
Margarine?

168
00:07:53,460 --> 00:07:55,100
What's poisonous about margarine?

169
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:57,200
The benzoic acid.

170
00:07:57,260 --> 00:07:59,260
