217
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:33,960
Or up out of the stomach,

218
00:10:34,030 --> 00:10:36,830
as the case may be.

219
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:43,130
What is it?

220
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:46,560
Fungus.

221
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:03,260
Help! Please!

222
00:11:03,330 --> 00:11:04,330
I need help!

223
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:13,500
Emily,your family's bodies have been,

224
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:16,230
uh,colonized

225
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:19,160
by a fungal organisms,kind of like a mold,

226
00:11:19,230 --> 00:11:21,160
that's growing inside of them.

227
00:11:21,230 --> 00:11:24,300
And normally the doctors would give them

228
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:26,160
an anti-fungal medication

229
00:11:26,230 --> 00:11:28,830
that kill the fungus and allow them to get better.

230
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:32,160
But you tried that,and it didn't work?

231
00:11:32,230 --> 00:11:34,160
Well...

232
00:11:34,230 --> 00:11:36,200
Mmm.

233
00:11:36,260 --> 00:11:38,830
In this case,um,

234
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:42,160
even though we have killed the-the fungus,

235
00:11:42,230 --> 00:11:45,500
the paralysis is still progressing.

236
00:11:45,560 --> 00:11:48,060
So we are trying to find out why that is.

237
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:53,360
I don't have any other family.

238
00:11:56,250 --> 00:11:57,960
You have to fix them.

239
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:06,200
This is our fungus.

240
00:12:06,260 --> 00:12:08,260
Take a look.

241
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,860
It's...

242
00:12:13,930 --> 00:12:15,930
beautiful.

243
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,700
Botrytis cinerea.

244
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:19,730
It's everywhere.

245
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,900
There're probably spores of it

246
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,930
in the air we're breathing right now.

247
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,600
Don't worry... it only,uh,

248
00:12:26,660 --> 00:12:27,930
grows on plants.

249
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,800
That's why it's on the food inside the dog,

250
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:32,800
but not actually on the dog's tissues itself.

251
00:12:32,860 --> 00:12:36,460
So Trixie ate whatever the family ate.

252
00:12:36,530 --> 00:12:37,800
Mm-hmm.

253
00:12:37,860 --> 00:12:40,600
And we know the family ate plant material...

254
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:42,930
fruits and vegetables...

255
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:45,960
but we don't know which fruits

256
00:12:46,030 --> 00:12:48,460
and/or vegetables were contaminated.

257
00:12:48,530 --> 00:12:51,160
There's our conundrum.

258
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:54,800
In its natural state,

259
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:58,430
botrytis cinerea is completely harmless to humans.

260
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:02,100
From the looks of that specimen,

261
00:13:02,160 --> 00:13:05,230
I'd say it's been genetically modified.

262
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:10,900
And it's not harmless anymore.

263
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:22,930
Care to explain why we're hunting a deadly fungus

264
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,360
in a wine shop?

265
00:13:24,430 --> 00:13:26,860
Because some winemakers use genetically modified fungus

266
00:13:26,930 --> 00:13:28,000
in their product.

267
00:13:28,060 --> 00:13:30,000
And Coppertina Vineyards

268
00:13:30,060 --> 00:13:32,100
is one of the world's leading makers

269
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:34,160
of botrytized wine.

270
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:38,230
Once upon a time

271
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:40,730
in Medieval France,there was a nobleman

272
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:43,730
who liked to oversee every aspect

273
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:45,530
of the winemaking in his domain.

274
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,900
Control freak.

275
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:48,730
Exactly.

276
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:51,530
