00:27:38,030 --> 00:27:41,500
You're lucky I'm not tempted to abuse my powers.

555
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:51,060
This should be it.

556
00:27:55,900 --> 00:27:58,160
Professor Altschuler?

557
00:28:02,600 --> 00:28:05,400
Professor Altschuler,it's the FBI.

558
00:28:08,630 --> 00:28:09,860
Let's try this.

559
00:28:28,560 --> 00:28:31,160
He's dead.

560
00:28:31,230 --> 00:28:33,100
Drug overdose?

561
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:35,530
I'll call the police.

562
00:28:47,830 --> 00:28:49,960
Fascinating.

563
00:28:50,030 --> 00:28:53,130
That's got the thickened tail

564
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:56,760
of the Androctonus crassicauda,but the size and coloring

565
00:28:56,830 --> 00:28:59,860
of the Leiurus quinquestriatus.

566
00:28:59,930 --> 00:29:01,760
But it's a scorpion.

567
00:29:01,830 --> 00:29:04,100
Yeah,it's a scorpion.

568
00:29:05,430 --> 00:29:07,760
But it's no species I've ever seen before.

569
00:29:07,830 --> 00:29:09,660
I expect a geneticist

570
00:29:09,730 --> 00:29:12,700
of Altschuler's caliber would be

571
00:29:12,760 --> 00:29:15,900
more than able to engineer a hybrid.

572
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:20,260
So,what are you,a bug expert,too?

573
00:29:20,330 --> 00:29:22,460
It's not a bug; it's an arachnid.

574
00:29:22,530 --> 00:29:24,800
And no,I'm no expert.

575
00:29:26,660 --> 00:29:28,200
Someone very close to me

576
00:29:28,260 --> 00:29:31,230
was,um,involved in an experimental

577
00:29:31,300 --> 00:29:35,930
brain cancer treatment that used scorpion venom.

578
00:29:39,300 --> 00:29:41,060
It was your wife...

579
00:29:41,130 --> 00:29:42,860
right?

580
00:29:44,830 --> 00:29:47,260
I... I know she died of cancer

581
00:29:47,330 --> 00:29:49,360
two years ago.

582
00:29:49,430 --> 00:29:54,000
Yeah,it was quite a promising treatment,actually,but,um...

583
00:29:54,060 --> 00:29:56,260
unfortunately,not quite on time.

584
00:30:00,830 --> 00:30:03,000
I'm sorry,Hood.

585
00:30:06,460 --> 00:30:08,160
This wasn't drug related.

586
00:30:10,660 --> 00:30:12,560
This was an overdose of scorpion venom.

587
00:30:12,630 --> 00:30:16,630
The thing about scorpions is they don't go for humans.

588
00:30:16,700 --> 00:30:18,700
They go for insects.

589
00:30:21,760 --> 00:30:23,530
That's it.

590
00:30:23,600 --> 00:30:25,560
It's a pesticide.

591
00:30:25,630 --> 00:30:27,500
What?

592
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:30,330
Oh,my God,it's brilliant.

593
00:30:30,400 --> 00:30:35,600
Scorpion venom is made to paralyze insects.

594
00:30:35,660 --> 00:30:39,600
If Altschuler could take the botrytis fungus

595
00:30:39,660 --> 00:30:42,460
and combine it with the scorpion venom,

596
00:30:42,530 --> 00:30:47,600
he would have a totally organic pesticide.

597
00:30:47,660 --> 00:30:50,160
To spray on the produce...

598
00:30:50,230 --> 00:30:52,200
to kill insects with the venom?

599
00:30:52,260 --> 00:30:54,630
And that is what

600
00:30:54,700 --> 00:30:58,360
has been paralyzing our victims.

601
00:30:58,430 --> 00:31:01,130
No bite marks or stings.

602
00:31:01,200 --> 00:31:05,130
And nobody's going to be checking for scorpion venom

603
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:08,200
because the only deadly scorpions native to the U.S.

604
00:31:08,260 --> 00:31:10,660
are in the Arizona desert.

605
00:31:10,730 --> 00:31:13,400
What I don't understand is

606
00:31:13,460 --> 00:31:15,960
why the venom was released in our victims

607
00:31:16,030 --> 00:31:19,160
when it's only supposed to attack insects.

608
00:31:19,230 --> 00:31:22,300
Or why it affected everyone in the Stanner family

609
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:23,660
except for Emily.

610
00:31:23,730 --> 00:31:26,330
We've got the bullet,but we don't have the trigger.

611
00:31:27,360 --> 00:31:32,360
No... but we have something else.

612
00:31:32,430 --> 00:31:34,360
Poor bastard.

613
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:39,130
He was trying to atone for the mess he made.

614
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:41,400
But to make enough antibodies

615
00:31:41,460 --> 00:31:43,000
to produce a scorpion antivenin,

616
00:31:43,060 --> 00:31:45,960
he'd have to endure sting after sting.

617
00:31:46,030 --> 00:31:49,360
Let's just hope the dose that killed him

618
00:31:49,430 --> 00:31:53,260
was enough to turn his blood...

619
00:31:53,330 --> 00:31:55,830
into a cure.

620
00:32:25,060 --> 00:32:27,460
Dr. Richards has the hospital toxicologist

621
00:32:27,530 --> 00:32:29,460
working on synthesizing an antivenin

622
00:32:29,530 --> 00:32:31,860
from Altschuler's blood.

623
00:32:31,930 --> 00:32:34,160
We'll just have to wait and see.

624
00:32:35,200 --> 00:32:37,130
You hungry?

625
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:39,030
No,I'm fine.

626
00:32:39,100 --> 00:32:40,960
Hood,you should eat something.

627
00:32:41,030 --> 00:32:43,630
You call that eating?

628
00:32:43,700 --> 00:32:46,560
I know,the sweet tooth.

629
00:32:57,560 --> 00:32:59,700
You could've just asked.

630
00:32:59,760 --> 00:33:01,030
This is it; this is the trigger.

631
00:33:01,100 --> 00:33:02,660
My candy?

632
00:33:02,730 --> 00:33:04,730
You know what's in this?

633
00:33:04,800 --> 00:33:06,930
"Licoricey" goodness?

634
00:33:07,960 --> 00:33:09,730
Insects.

635
00:33:11,560 --> 00:33:14,500
Carmine. It's a red food coloring

636
00:33:14,560 --> 00:33:16,560
made from a South American beetle.

637
00:33:18,560 --> 00:33:20,100
I'm suddenly in the mood for some fresh produce.

638
00:33:26,030 --> 00:33:28,360
Have you had breakfast yet,Mr.Cooper?

639
00:33:32,860 --> 00:33:34,760
Strawberries,maybe?

640
00:33:34,830 --> 00:33:36,860
Rachel,what did the Stanners have for breakfast?

641
00:33:36,930 --> 00:33:39,700
Corn flakes,pancakes,fruit salad...

642
00:33:39,760 --> 00:33:41,060
grapefruit juice?

643
00:33:41,130 --> 00:33:44,000
Pink grapefruit juice made with carmine.

644
00:33:44,060 --> 00:33:45,760
And the fruit salad

645
00:33:45,830 --> 00:33:50,060
probably contained fungus from your pesticide.

646
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:52,830
The Sheridan family.

647
00:33:52,900 --> 00:33:54,630
Oh,the Sheridan family,

648
00:33:54,700 --> 00:33:56,830
they ate any number of fruits and vegetables for dinner.

649
00:33:56,900 --> 00:34:01,430
Finished with red velvet cake,carmine red.

650
00:34:02,460 --> 00:34:04,500
It's a synergy effect.

651
00:34:04,560 --> 00:34:06,730
See,the fungus,

652
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:09,400
it attacks the insect proteins.

653
00:34:09,460 --> 00:34:11,760
It doesn't know they've already been eaten by a human.

654
00:34:11,830 --> 00:34:14,130
So the fungus is the loaded gun,

655
00:34:14,200 --> 00:34:16,860
and the food coloring containing the insect proteins

656
00:34:16,930 --> 00:34:18,930
is the trigger.

657
00:34:21,200 --> 00:34:24,030
Around two years

658
00:34:24,100 --> 00:34:26,360
and several million dollars into the project,

659
00:34:26,430 --> 00:34:29,060
we decided that the end product

660
00:34:29,130 --> 00:34:30,830
wasn't viable anymore.

661
00:34:30,900 --> 00:34:35,360
You see,when we fed our test animals food which was dusted

662
00:34:35,430 --> 00:34:39,200
with the,uh,pesticide,see,most of them were fine.

663
00:34:39,260 --> 00:34:40,430
Except for one.

664
00:34:40,500 --> 00:34:41,930
Which was paralyzed.

665
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:44,130
I mean,we did everything by the book,

666
00:34:44,200 --> 00:34:45,630
you know,for a phase three trial.

667
00:34:45,700 --> 00:34:46,730
The test sample sizes,

668
00:34:46,800 --> 00:34:49,800
genetic lines,everything.

669
00:34:49,860 --> 00:34:53,460
And I thought it was just some kind of anomaly,

670
00:34:53,530 --> 00:34:54,930
but Altschuler,of course,he was obsessed,

671
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:57,600
so he,he did a culture of the dead animal's body,

672
00:34:57,660 --> 00:34:59,100
ran all kinds of tests and...

673
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:03,000
And that's when he discovered the fatal synergy.

674
00:35:04,860 --> 00:35:06,560
We stopped the project before it went any further.

675
00:35:06,630 --> 00:35:09,830
We sent what was left to a biowaste disposal facility,

676
00:35:09,900 --> 00:35:11,630
and that was that.

677
00:35:11,700 --> 00:35:13,030
Until now.

678
00:35:13,100 --> 00:35:14,530
You should have contacted the authorities

679
00:35:14,600 --> 00:35:17,000
the minute you suspected something.

680
00:35:17,060 --> 00:35:19,260
If those people die,it's negligent homicide.

681
00:35:19,330 --> 00:35:21,000
No,uh,you got to believe me here.

682
00:35:21,060 --> 00:35:23,700
I have all the paperwork on file,

683
00:35:23,760 --> 00:35:26,460
uh,all of our waste goes to a federally licensed

684
00:35:26,530 --> 00:35:28,700
disposal facility just east of here.

685
00:35:28,760 --> 00:35:31,530
It's a 45-minute drive.

686
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:37,830
All right,all right!

687
00:35:37,900 --> 00:35:39,100
Nice and easy!

688
00:35:39,160 --> 00:35:41,000
Two-three-five- eight- seven-zero-one.

689
00:35:41,060 --> 00:35:42,060
This one checks out.

690
00:35:42,130 --> 00:35:44,000
- Where are the rest?  - That's it!

691
00:35:44,060 --> 00:35:46,300
Ground radar confirms we got

692
00:35:46,360 --> 00:35:47,600
ten tanks of pesticides.

693
00:35:47,660 --> 00:35:49,130
There should be 14.

694
00:35:49,200 --> 00:35:51,900
We're going to have to question all these workers,

695
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:54,630
anyone whose had access to the disposal field

696
00:35:54,700 --> 00:35:56,760
in the past 12 months.

697
00:36:01,960 --> 00:36:03,000
Hood,car!

698
00:37:03,460 --> 00:37:06,660
Where are the four missing canisters of Aeonium pesticide?

699
00:37:06,730 --> 00:37:08,460
People are going to die!

700
00:37:08,530 --> 00:37:09,930
- Tell me!  - O-Okay...

701
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:12,960
Okay! I-I gave them to my dad.

702
00:37:13,030 --> 00:37:14,930
I just wanted to help him out a little,

703
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:16,430
that's all!

704
00:37:16,500 --> 00:37:17,500
And it did!

705
00:37:18,200 --> 00:37:20,460
Rachel...

706
00:37:28,430 --> 00:37:30,130
Sir!

707
00:37:30,200 --> 00:37:32,200
Put the can down!

708
00:37:32,260 --> 00:37:33,930
You get away.

709
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:36,360
My boy called me and told me to burn the fields.

710
00:37:36,430 --> 00:37:37,860
That's exactly what I'm doing.

711
00:37:38,900 --> 00:37:41,760
People are sick because you put

712
00:37:41,830 --> 00:37:43,930
Aeonium pesticides in your crops.

713
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:46,760
You put the lives of every person who ate

714
00:37:46,830 --> 00:37:48,430
produce from your farm at serious risk.

715
00:37:48,500 --> 00:37:50,630
By burning your fields,

716
00:37:50,700 --> 00:37:53,260
there's a very good chance you're going to spread

717
00:37:53,330 --> 00:37:55,000
whatever organism made those people sick

718
00:37:55,060 --> 00:37:56,060
to the neighboring farms.

719
00:37:57,160 --> 00:37:59,360
You see those fields over there?

720
00:37:59,430 --> 00:38:01,960
Monsanto.

721
00:38:02,030 --> 00:38:03,960
You see these fields over here?

722
00:38:04,030 --> 00:38:06,260
Crops all the way to the base of those mountains?

723
00:38:06,330 --> 00:38:07,460
That's Dole.

724
00:38:07,530 --> 00:38:10,460
When my father's father

725
00:38:10,530 --> 00:38:13,500
settled this land,it was small family farms

726
00:38:13,560 --> 00:38:16,730
for as far as the eye could see.

727
00:38:16,800 --> 00:38:18,930
Now,we're the only ones left.

728
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:20,760
Drop it,now.

729
00:38:21,730 --> 00:38:24,160
Last year we almost lost this place.

730
00:38:24,230 --> 00:38:26,960
Yeah,when we planted the new crop

731
00:38:27,030 --> 00:38:28,900
my boy called me and he said,

732
00:38:28,960 --> 00:38:32,360
"Dad," he says,"I got something that we can put on the crops

733
00:38:32,430 --> 00:38:35,900
"that'll really make a difference."

734
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:37,360
So we put it on there.

735
00:38:37,430 --> 00:38:39,560
We used it,yes,sir.

736
00:38:39,630 --> 00:38:41,030
Now,I knew where it come from.

737
00:38:41,100 --> 00:38:42,460
It worked so good,I didn question it.

738
00:38:42,530 --> 00:38:45,030
Well,maybe you should have.

739
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:53,760
That's the state police.

740
00:38:56,600 --> 00:38:58,860
It's over,sir.

741
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:05,930
Well,I'll,uh...

742
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:08,160
I'll,I'll go with you.

743
00:39:08,230 --> 00:39:11,360
I'm sorry about what we did.

744
00:39:11,430 --> 00:39:13,400
I'm real sorry.

745
00:39:28,660 --> 00:39:30,400
Mom,Dad,this is Dr. Hood.

746
00:39:30,460 --> 00:39:32,230
He's the only one that believed

747
00:39:32,300 --> 00:39:33,930
I wasn't trying to poison you guys.

748
00:39:34,860 --> 00:39:35,900
Thank you.

749
00:39:35,960 --> 00:39:37,560
Oh,don't mention it.

750
00:39:37,630 --> 00:39:40,800
I'm just glad the scorpion antivenin worked.

751
00:39:40,860 --> 00:39:44,660
But Emily still needs to see a chemistry tutor.

752
00:39:59,630 --> 00:40:02,130
We were lucky.

753
00:40:02,200 --> 00:40:05,960
Fungus tends to mutate really quickly.

754
00:40:06,030 --> 00:40:08,000
Sooner or later,there'd be a hardier strain

755
00:40:08,060 --> 00:40:10,060
and way more people would've been at risk.

756
00:40:10,130 --> 00:40:13,700
Guess I'm going to have to look at my food labels

757
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:15,400
more closely from now on.

758
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:22,230
Uh,natural coloring.

759
00:40:22,300 --> 00:40:24,660
So,you're saying that's just bugs,huh?

760
00:40:24,730 --> 00:40:27,000
Maybe,maybe not.

761
00:40:27,060 --> 00:40:28,660
According to the FDA

762
00:40:28,730 --> 00:40:30,860
as long as it's "natural" it could be anything.

763
00:40:32,900 --> 00:40:36,530
Green food coloring,on the other hand,

764
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:41,500
is a petroleum derived triphenylmethane.

765
00:40:41,560 --> 00:40:43,330
Nothing natural about it.

766
00:40:46,100 --> 00:40:47,830
Yummy.

